OL,6,FA draft report into the boy's death by
OL,7,FNiche Health and Social Care
OL,8,FConsulting, carried out as a response
OL,9,Fto the family's complaints, has now
OL,10,Ffound some of his care did not meet
OL,11,Fexpected standards. It made 15
OL,12,Frecommendations.
OL,14,FThe report concluded that some changes
OL,15,F` such as earlier escalation to
OL,16,Fintensive care, earlier insertion of a
OL,17,Fchest drain and earlier intubation `
OL,18,Fmay have marginally increased his
OL,19,Fchances of survival. But it said they
OL,20,Fwere ultimately unlikely to have
OL,21,Fchanged the outcome.
